Subject: [PATCH] panfrost: add Mali-G710 (felix / Tensor G2) model entry

felix reports gpu_id 0xa862; masked with the Valhall 0xff0f0000 mask that
is 0xa8020000 -> prod_id 0xa802 (Valhall arch 10.8, prod 2), variant 0.
Without a model entry Mesa rejects the GPU ("Unknown GPU ID"). G710 is
architecturally G610 with more cores, so reuse the G610 model params.

NOTE — the model table location and prod-id encoding differ by Mesa version:

 * Mesa 25.2.x: src/panfrost/lib/pan_props.c, raw hex prod id. Add after the
   G610 (0xa807) VALHALL_MODEL row:
     VALHALL_MODEL(0xa802, 0, "G710", "TVIx", MODEL_ANISO(ALL),
                   MODEL_TB_SIZES(32768, 16384), MODEL_RATES(4, 8, 64)),

 * Mesa main (>= the pan_model split): src/panfrost/model/pan_model.c, using
   the PAN_PROD_ID(arch_major, arch_minor, prod_major) macro. 0xa802 becomes
   PAN_PROD_ID(10, 8, 2) (G610 is PAN_PROD_ID(10, 8, 7)). Add after the G610
   row:
     VALHALL_MODEL(PAN_PROD_ID(10, 8, 2), 0, "G710", "TVIx", MODEL_ANISO(ALL),
                   MODEL_TB_SIZES(32768, 16384), MODEL_RATES(4, 8, 64)),

This is the change carried on the `felix-g710` branch of
github.com/junkyard-computing/mesa (committed against Mesa main), built for
the device via `nix run .#build-mesa`.
